narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Overview of different topics in physical organic chemstry, including guest-host interactions, acid-base concepts, and pericyclic reactions.
Organic chemistry and physical organic chemistry
Introduction to relevance of physical organic chemistry to medicinal chemistry and host-guest chemistry, pericyclic reactions

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Lecture notes very detailed, however a little messy and hard to read. Professor very knowledgable. Lectures covered useful material, but were not very engaging.

Strengths: discussed some interesting concepts

Weaknesses: assumed a lot of background FMOT (would have been helpful to have gone through an introductory example or assign an introductory reading). Graded problem sets throughout semester would have been very helpful.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: No, I would not. I did not retain much of what I learned.
